213
00:12:44,067 --> 00:12:47,505
What do we do to catch up?

214
00:12:47,636 --> 00:12:49,029
[sighs]

215
00:12:49,159 --> 00:12:50,465
I don't know.

216
00:12:55,122 --> 00:12:56,732
ROBERT: Nothing ever
changes in this town.

217
00:12:56,863 --> 00:12:59,256
ORRIN MERCER: It sure is pretty.

218
00:12:59,387 --> 00:13:01,215
You must've lovedgrowing up here as a kid.

219
00:13:04,392 --> 00:13:08,875
You know, Orrin, I
couldn't wait to leave.

220
00:13:09,005 --> 00:13:10,702
How do we fix it?

221
00:13:10,833 --> 00:13:12,226
Are the chips still dirty?

222
00:13:12,356 --> 00:13:13,488
No, I think we've
got that licked.

223
00:13:13,618 --> 00:13:14,532
