I am gonna take this home,and I am gonna figure

541
00:30:05,891 --> 00:30:08,894
out what is wrong with it.

542
00:30:09,024 --> 00:30:11,331
I'll see you later, Orrin.

543
00:30:11,461 --> 00:30:13,333
See you later.

544
00:30:13,463 --> 00:30:14,334
[door opens]

545
00:30:15,335 --> 00:30:18,338
[chattering]

546
00:31:05,864 --> 00:31:07,213
[groans]

547
00:31:10,520 --> 00:31:11,957
Hello.

548
00:31:12,087 --> 00:31:13,567
EVIE: Oh, Good
morning, Mr. Cannon.

549
00:31:13,697 --> 00:31:14,655
Good morning

550
00:31:14,785 --> 00:31:16,657
[birds calling]

551
00:31:16,787 --> 00:31:23,533
I, um-- I'd like to renta boat, uh, nothing fancy.

552
00:31:23,664 --> 00:31:26,188
Um, maybe one of
these thingies here.

553
00:31:26,319 --> 00:31:28,408
Oh, well, there's
nothing available.

554
00:31:28,538 --> 00:31:30,018
Two of them are booked
out this afternoon,

555
00:31:30,149 --> 00:31:32,020
and the other one
needs servicing.

556
00:31:32,151 --> 00:31:33,326
Is that a big problem?

557
00:31:33,456 --> 00:31:36,720
No, it's just regular
servicing, but--

558
00:31:36,851 --> 00:31:38,722
So can you service it?

559
00:31:38,853 --> 00:31:41,987
Well, I'm going to
later this afternoon.

560
00:31:42,117 --> 00:31:44,119
How about now?

561
00:31:44,250 --> 00:31:46,817
I'm busy now.

562
00:31:46,948 --> 00:31:48,341
What's the big rush?

563
00:31:48,471 --> 00:31:49,255
Oh, I'm sorry.

564
00:31:51,387 --> 00:31:52,649
I'm sorry.
I just wanted--

565
00:31:52,780 --> 00:31:54,347
I wanted to get out there.

566
00:31:54,477 --> 00:31:56,436
And I wanted to, uh, find thespot where they found him.

567
00:32:00,048 --> 00:32:02,398
I'm almost finished.

568
00:32:02,529 --> 00:32:03,660
Thank you.

569
00:32:03,791 --> 00:32:04,531
I'll just wait.

570
00:32:09,144 --> 00:32:10,493
[engine starts]

571
00:32:10,624 --> 00:32:11,886
I'll see you later.

572
00:32:12,017 --> 00:32:12,756
Thanks again.

573
00:32:12,887 --> 00:32:13,670
[engine roars]

574
00:32:13,801 --> 00:32:14,584
Whoa!

575
00:32:14,715 --> 00:32:15,890
Whoa.

576
00:32:16,021 --> 00:32:19,285
EVIE: You might
wanna cast off first.

577
00:32:19,415 --> 00:32:20,199
[engine roars]

578
00:32:20,329 --> 00:32:21,026
Whoa!

579
00:32:23,637 --> 00:32:24,768
I don't know where I'm going.

580
00:32:24,899 --> 00:32:25,682
I'll draw you a map.

581
00:32:29,643 --> 00:32:30,818
Um, OK.

582
00:32:34,169 --> 00:32:38,782
This is Shad's Passage
right here, right?

583
00:32:38,913 --> 00:32:41,611
Now, right here,
as you go along,

584
00:32:41,742 --> 00:32:44,484
there will be a dock
on the left, OK?

585
00:32:44,614 --> 00:32:48,314
And just past that, there'sa white navigation marker.

586
00:32:48,444 --> 00:32:49,968
That's where they
found Kevin's body.

587
00:32:58,585 --> 00:33:01,980
[beeping]

588
00:33:21,086 --> 00:33:24,393
[birds calling]

589
00:33:57,513 --> 00:34:00,864
[music playing]

590
00:34:38,424 --> 00:34:39,773
[sighs]

591
00:34:43,907 --> 00:34:46,780
[engine sputtering]

592
00:34:47,911 --> 00:34:50,740
[groaning]

593
00:34:51,872 --> 00:34:52,742
Oh, perfect.

594
00:34:56,442 --> 00:34:57,269
Oh.

595
00:34:57,399 --> 00:34:58,574
Oh, ah, hey!

596
00:34:58,705 --> 00:35:00,576
Ah!

597
00:35:00,707 --> 00:35:02,187
Oh.

598
00:35:02,317 --> 00:35:03,057
Shoot.

599
00:35:21,728 --> 00:35:22,468
Hey!

600
00:35:25,601 --> 00:35:27,560
Over here!

601
00:35:27,690 --> 00:35:28,474
Robert!

602
00:35:35,089 --> 00:35:36,438
[sighs]

603
00:35:48,537 --> 00:35:50,365
[laughing]

604
00:35:52,585 --> 00:35:54,630
I think the proper nauticalterm is "ahoy there."

605
00:35:54,761 --> 00:35:55,501
Yeah, well.

606
00:35:55,631 --> 00:35:56,458
[sighs]

607
00:35:56,589 --> 00:35:58,504
Are you OK?

608
00:35:58,634 --> 00:36:00,245
Yeah, I'm fine.

609
00:36:00,375 --> 00:36:01,289
Well, what happened?

610
00:36:01,420 --> 00:36:02,725
You were supposed to be back.

611
00:36:02,856 --> 00:36:05,337
Well, what happened was
this perfectly reliable

612
00:36:05,467 --> 00:36:06,642
engine of yours stalled.
- Mhm.

613
00:36:06,773 --> 00:36:07,861
- That's what happened.
- Mm.

614
00:36:07,991 --> 00:36:09,602
Well, I'm surprised
you didn't use

615
00:36:09,732 --> 00:36:11,604
your mobile phone to call yourinternational headquarters.

616
00:36:11,734 --> 00:36:12,518
Yeah, well, I--

617
00:36:12,648 --> 00:36:13,997
I forgot it.

618
00:36:14,128 --> 00:36:14,911
Mm.

619
00:36:15,042 --> 00:36:15,999
Mhm.

620
00:36:16,130 --> 00:36:17,262
Do you wanna throw me a line?

621
00:36:17,392 --> 00:36:18,132
Where?

622
00:36:18,263 --> 00:36:19,046
Over there?

623
00:36:19,177 --> 00:36:20,308
Mhm.

624
00:36:20,439 --> 00:36:21,179
Ah.

625
00:36:23,442 --> 00:36:25,226
EVIE: You don't have a line?

626
00:36:25,357 --> 00:36:26,662
I don't see any line.

627
00:36:26,793 --> 00:36:27,663
EVIE: [scoffs]

628
00:36:29,752 --> 00:36:33,103
[birds calling]

629
00:36:41,634 --> 00:36:42,896
Come here.

630
00:36:43,026 --> 00:36:44,114
I wanna show you something.

631
00:36:52,427 --> 00:36:53,341
[groans]

632
00:36:53,472 --> 00:36:54,212
See?

633
00:36:57,563 --> 00:37:00,000
I, uh-- I guess that
explains what happened.

634
00:37:00,130 --> 00:37:01,349
That's OK.
It happens.

635
00:37:01,480 --> 00:37:02,568
- Mhm.
- Come on, I'll tow you.

636
00:37:05,745 --> 00:37:07,050
[bird squawking]

637
00:37:15,189 --> 00:37:16,234
You see that over there?

638
00:37:16,364 --> 00:37:18,975
That there is Spyglass Hill.

639
00:37:19,106 --> 00:37:19,933
No, it's not.

640
00:37:20,063 --> 00:37:22,196
It's called Gibbons Bluff.

641
00:37:22,327 --> 00:37:23,676
Nope.

642
00:37:23,806 --> 00:37:25,547
That's called Spyglass Hill.

643
00:37:25,678 --> 00:37:29,247
That's the name Kevin and Igave it when we were kids.

644
00:37:29,377 --> 00:37:33,729
It's a haven for
smugglers and pirates.

645
00:37:33,860 --> 00:37:36,515
He used to spend
hours up there looking

646
00:37:36,645 --> 00:37:38,778
out for British men of war.

647
00:37:38,908 --> 00:37:40,083
That's cute.

648
00:37:40,214 --> 00:37:41,868
ROBERT: A lot of
people died around here

649
00:37:41,998 --> 00:37:47,874
looking for buried treasure,out here and down by Oak Island.

650
00:37:48,004 --> 00:37:49,571
During Prohibition,
they used to smuggle

651
00:37:49,702 --> 00:37:53,445
booze from here down to Boston.

652
00:37:53,575 --> 00:37:57,275
Piracy in these parts has hada long and venerable tradition.

653
00:38:19,297 --> 00:38:20,080
Is there, uh--

654
00:38:20,210 --> 00:38:21,124
[clears throat]

655
00:38:21,255 --> 00:38:22,561
--any decent restaurant in town?

656
00:38:22,691 --> 00:38:24,171
God knows there
wasn't when I grew up.

657
00:38:24,302 --> 00:38:25,564
I'm starving.

658
00:38:25,694 --> 00:38:27,000
- Why don't I make you dinner.- No.

659
00:38:27,130 --> 00:38:28,523
No, no, no, I didn't mean that.

660
00:38:28,654 --> 00:38:30,743
Uh, you've done more thanenough, uh, for today,

661
00:38:30,873 --> 00:38:31,744
thank you.

662
00:38:31,874 --> 00:38:32,614
I'm actually a good cook.

663
00:38:32,745 --> 00:38:33,920
No, I believe you are.

664
00:38:34,050 --> 00:38:36,444
But, uh, no, I'll just--

665
00:38:36,575 --> 00:38:37,402
I'll just go home.

666
00:38:37,532 --> 00:38:38,707
And make a box of cereal.

667
00:38:38,838 --> 00:38:40,274
No, I was thinking
a can of beans.

668
00:38:40,405 --> 00:38:42,450
I have to shop anyway.

669
00:38:42,581 --> 00:38:43,712
OK, yes.

670
00:38:43,843 --> 00:38:44,887
Great.

671
00:38:45,018 --> 00:38:46,149
- Can I use your phone?
- Sure.

672
00:38:46,280 --> 00:38:47,194
I'll be right back.

673
00:38:47,325 --> 00:38:50,676
I just wanna call the office.

674
00:38:50,806 --> 00:38:51,764
[door opens]

675
00:38:52,591 --> 00:38:53,156
[dial tone]

676
00:38:53,287 --> 00:38:54,157
[door closes]

677
00:38:56,899 --> 00:38:58,161
[siren wailing]

678
00:38:58,292 --> 00:38:59,119
BEECHAM [ON PHONE]:
This is Ellen Beecham.

679
00:38:59,249 --> 00:39:00,163
ROBERT [ON PHONE]: Beecham.

680
00:39:00,294 --> 00:39:01,861
BEECHAM [ON PHONE]: Hey, boss.

681
00:39:01,991 --> 00:39:03,645
I faxed you the informationyou asked about on Ms. Shaw.

682
00:39:03,776 --> 00:39:04,820
ROBERT [ON PHONE]: Uh-huh.

683
00:39:04,951 --> 00:39:06,605
You turn up anything
interesting?

684
00:39:06,735 --> 00:39:10,086
She looks pretty ordinary onpaper, except for her picture.

685
00:39:10,217 --> 00:39:11,131
She's very attractive.

686
00:39:11,261 --> 00:39:13,089
Uh-huh, uh-huh.
What else?

687
00:39:13,220 --> 00:39:15,091
BEECHAM [ON PHONE]: Well, Ialso got a line on a housekeeper

688
00:39:15,222 --> 00:39:17,267
for you-- uh, a
couple, actually.

689
00:39:17,398 --> 00:39:19,182
She does the cooking, thecleaning, the shopping.

690
00:39:19,313 --> 00:39:20,662
And he does the gardeningand the driving.

691
00:39:20,793 --> 00:39:21,750
No.

692
00:39:21,881 --> 00:39:22,838
No, that will not be necessary.

693
00:39:22,969 --> 00:39:24,449
Well, you sure, boss?

694
00:39:24,579 --> 00:39:25,711
I mean, I know you're onlygonna be there a few days,

695
00:39:25,841 --> 00:39:26,886
but it will make you
more comfortable.

696
00:39:27,016 --> 00:39:27,930
ROBERT [ON PHONE]: No, I, uh--

697
00:39:28,061 --> 00:39:29,323
[door opens]

698
00:39:29,454 --> 00:39:31,281
I'd rather be alone.

699
00:39:31,412 --> 00:39:33,719
OK, well, if you need
them, give me a call.

700
00:39:33,849 --> 00:39:35,068
I've got their number.

701
00:39:35,198 --> 00:39:36,939
What would I do without you?

702
00:39:37,070 --> 00:39:40,378
Uh, if you do, uh, go home,uh, be sure to let me know.

703
00:39:40,508 --> 00:39:42,336
Boss, you know I always
sleep at the office.

704
00:39:42,467 --> 00:39:43,729
Attagirl.

705
00:39:43,859 --> 00:39:44,599
Thank you.

706
00:39:48,081 --> 00:39:49,082
How much do you
pay that woman?

707
00:39:49,212 --> 00:39:50,388
Beecham?

708
00:39:50,518 --> 00:39:53,347
Not enough.

709
00:39:53,478 --> 00:39:56,045
Let's go.

710
00:39:56,176 --> 00:39:57,482
ROBERT: I can't believe this.

711
00:39:57,612 --> 00:39:59,788
They got 15 different
types of olives here.

712
00:39:59,919 --> 00:40:01,660
Things sure have changed
since I was a kid.

713
00:40:01,790 --> 00:40:04,445
Yeah, well, they even havearugula and Reggiano-Parmesan.

714
00:40:04,576 --> 00:40:06,926
Yes, and fresh
seafood on the coast.

715
00:40:07,056 --> 00:40:07,970
Can you believe it?

716
00:40:08,101 --> 00:40:08,884
Oh.

717
00:40:09,015 --> 00:40:09,798
Oops.

718
00:40:09,929 --> 00:40:10,712
[laughs]

719
00:40:10,843 --> 00:40:11,800
You're a little excited.

720
00:40:11,931 --> 00:40:12,932
I'm gonna go get the wine.

721
00:40:13,062 --> 00:40:13,846
I'll do the shop.

722
00:40:16,849 --> 00:40:19,982
[chattering]

723
00:40:21,114 --> 00:40:22,463
Boy, oh boy, real food.

724
00:40:22,594 --> 00:40:23,595
You really know
what you're doing.

725
00:40:23,725 --> 00:40:24,596
[laughs]

726
00:40:24,726 --> 00:40:25,553
You, I'm not so sure about.

727
00:40:25,684 --> 00:40:26,424
No, I-- I don't know.

728
00:40:26,554 --> 00:40:28,164
I was going for healthy.

729
00:40:28,295 --> 00:40:29,688
But then, you know, I startedgetting all these cravings.

730
00:40:29,818 --> 00:40:31,559
And I got-- I got
caught in a time warp.

731
00:40:31,690 --> 00:40:32,952
But, uh, listen.

732
00:40:33,082 --> 00:40:34,475
[ITALIAN ACCENT] Smell this.Mm, that aroma.

733
00:40:34,606 --> 00:40:36,216
Mm, yeah.

734
00:40:36,346 --> 00:40:37,130
With that diet, I don't knowhow you made it through puberty.

735
00:40:37,260 --> 00:40:38,697
- I didn't.
- [laughs]

736
00:40:38,827 --> 00:40:39,872
[ITALIAN ACCENT] Here,let me, uh-- let me, please.

737
00:40:40,002 --> 00:40:40,655
- No, no.
- No, no, please.

738
00:40:40,786 --> 00:40:41,526
No.

739
00:40:41,656 --> 00:40:44,093
No, please, let-- oh.

740
00:40:44,224 --> 00:40:45,312
Let me get this.

741
00:40:45,443 --> 00:40:46,182
[beep]

742
00:40:46,313 --> 00:40:47,183
[cash register whirring]

743
00:40:47,314 --> 00:40:50,056
[waves lapping]

744
00:40:52,101 --> 00:40:54,843
You are one great cook.

745
00:40:54,974 --> 00:40:56,236
Oh, thank you.

746
00:40:56,366 --> 00:40:58,064
I used to cater in California.

747
00:40:58,194 --> 00:40:59,282
It was really nice to do this.

748
00:40:59,413 --> 00:41:00,675
I haven't done this
in a long time.

749
00:41:00,806 --> 00:41:02,764
That's a far cry from
catering in California

750
00:41:02,895 --> 00:41:05,419
to running a marina out here.

751
00:41:05,550 --> 00:41:06,333
True.

752
00:41:06,464 --> 00:41:07,247
[laughs]

753
00:41:09,075 --> 00:41:11,381
Must've been pretty toughafter your husband died, huh?

754
00:41:11,512 --> 00:41:13,166
It was, but not in
the way that you think.

755
00:41:13,296 --> 00:41:14,863
What do you mean?

756
00:41:14,994 --> 00:41:16,648
It was a big surprise.

757
00:41:16,778 --> 00:41:18,998
Why?

758
00:41:19,128 --> 00:41:20,695
It was an accident.

759
00:41:20,826 --> 00:41:22,958
Oh.

760
00:41:23,089 --> 00:41:25,047
How many years were you married?

761
00:41:25,178 --> 00:41:26,701
Three years.

762
00:41:26,832 --> 00:41:28,616
We met in California.
We got married.

763
00:41:28,747 --> 00:41:30,879
And then we came here
and bought the marina.

764
00:41:31,010 --> 00:41:35,318
Now why would you wannago from California to here?

765
00:41:35,449 --> 00:41:37,016
It was Grant's dream.

766
00:41:37,146 --> 00:41:40,498
He wanted to get away
from the rat race.

767
00:41:40,628 --> 00:41:43,501
Why'd you stay?

768
00:41:43,631 --> 00:41:46,025
His life insurance
paid for the mortgage.

769
00:41:46,155 --> 00:41:49,332
And I mean, I could've
sold it and left.

770
00:41:49,463 --> 00:41:51,204
But then I realized
that I loved it here.

771
00:41:51,334 --> 00:41:57,602
And it gave me a
sense of independence.

772
00:41:57,732 --> 00:41:59,604
Sometimes I feel
guilty for that.

773
00:41:59,734 --> 00:42:02,432
Because his death
bought you your freedom?

774
00:42:02,563 --> 00:42:04,870
No.

775
00:42:05,000 --> 00:42:07,176
We got married too fast.

776
00:42:07,307 --> 00:42:10,266
Grant had this way about him.

777
00:42:10,397 --> 00:42:12,138
He was hard to resist.

778
00:42:12,268 --> 00:42:13,008
So what changed?

779
00:42:16,969 --> 00:42:18,100
You ever wake
up in the morning

780
00:42:18,231 --> 00:42:19,101
and you're not in
love with someone?

781
00:42:23,845 --> 00:42:25,543
I felt relieved that I
didn't have to tell him.

782
00:42:28,241 --> 00:42:29,329
So--
[sighs]

783
00:42:29,459 --> 00:42:30,286
--have you ever been married?

784
00:42:33,725 --> 00:42:34,987
Um, no.

785
00:42:35,117 --> 00:42:36,554
So Kevin's your only family.

786
00:42:36,684 --> 00:42:40,470
Well, our parents
died when I was 18.

787
00:42:40,601 --> 00:42:42,516
Kevin was about six.

788
00:42:42,647 --> 00:42:45,475
I guess I became more of
a father than a brother

789
00:42:45,606 --> 00:42:47,086
to him at that point.

790
00:42:47,216 --> 00:42:48,566
You did a great job.

791
00:42:48,696 --> 00:42:49,958
No, this had
nothing to do with me.

792
00:42:50,089 --> 00:42:52,831
This was entirely his doing.

793
00:42:52,961 --> 00:42:57,618
He was a pretty, um,
engaging little kid.

794
00:42:57,749 --> 00:42:58,793
[laughs]

795
00:42:58,924 --> 00:43:01,100
Never complained
about anything.

796
00:43:01,230 --> 00:43:02,623
I, on the other
hand, as a parent,

797
00:43:02,754 --> 00:43:05,147
was completely hopeless.

798
00:43:05,278 --> 00:43:07,410
Mm.

799
00:43:07,541 --> 00:43:09,064
One time I took
him to the movies,

800
00:43:09,195 --> 00:43:12,241
when I was in college,with some friends of mine.

801
00:43:12,372 --> 00:43:14,374
After the, uh,
film was over, I--

802
00:43:14,504 --> 00:43:17,943
I forgot all about him, andI left him in the theater.

803
00:43:18,073 --> 00:43:19,118
That's awful.

804
00:43:19,248 --> 00:43:21,163
About an hour
and a half later,

805
00:43:21,294 --> 00:43:22,121
I realized what I had done.

806
00:43:22,251 --> 00:43:23,209
So I went--

807
00:43:23,339 --> 00:43:24,906
I bolted back there.

808
00:43:25,037 --> 00:43:30,869
And there he was, sittingexactly where I left him.

809
00:43:30,999 --> 00:43:31,783
He hadn't budged.

810
00:43:31,913 --> 00:43:33,480
[laughs]

